Hi Jimmy,

Yes, that looks right to me. If root zone depletion is negative, the
amount of water in the root zone is greater than the field
capacity. E.g. if root zone depletion is -0.5m, recharge becomes --0.5m
-> +0.5m, since the negative of a negative is a positive. If the root
zone depletion is positive the field capacity is not exceeded, so there
is no recharge.

All that being said, I'm currently revisiting this formulation because
I'm not getting sensible results for the groundwater levels. I'll keep
you updated.

Cheers,
